<subSubSection id="FC8E653B875BB1011CE35EB5F76CF5B2" pageId="20" pageNumber="213" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="B42B36B0875BB1011CE35EB5F7F2F6E9" blockId="20.[1978,2573,2215,2639]" pageId="20" pageNumber="213">
<emphasis id="86E0EAA2875BB1011CE35EB5F7C1F739" bold="true" box="[1978,2133,2215,2244]" pageId="20" pageNumber="213">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="73944D33875BB10113365EB5F7C2F711" authorityName="Merriam" authorityYear="1889" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Perognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="20" pageNumber="213" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="californicus">Perognathus californicus Merriam, 1889</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation id="04FC3CED875BB10113355EC1F7F2F6E9" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3802894326" pageId="20" pageNumber="213">Berkeley, Alameda Co., California, USA.</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B42B36B0875BB1011CE25F0BF76CF5B2" blockId="20.[1978,2573,2215,2639]" pageId="20" pageNumber="213">
Based on detailed sequencing of nDNA and mtDNA genes, 
<taxonomicName id="73944D33875BB101138B5F53F61CF69F" authorityName="Merriam" authorityYear="1889" box="[2258,2440,2369,2402]" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Perognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="20" pageNumber="215" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="californicus">C. californicus</taxonomicName>
is a close relative of 
<taxonomicName id="73944D33875BB10113035F7AF75EF674" baseAuthorityName="Merriam" baseAuthorityYear="1889" box="[2138,2250,2408,2441]" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Chaetodipus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="20" pageNumber="213" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fallax">C. fallax</taxonomicName>
, and both are part of the Baja California Peninsula lineage of the “modern” clade of coarse-haired pocket mice, along with C. ammophilus, 
<taxonomicName id="73944D33875BB1011CE75C1CF7CDF5DA" baseAuthorityName="Merriam" baseAuthorityYear="1894" box="[1982,2137,2574,2599]" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Chaetodipus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="20" pageNumber="213" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="arenarius">C. arenarius</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="73944D33875BB10113325C1CF741F5DA" baseAuthorityName="Osgood" baseAuthorityYear="1907" box="[2155,2261,2574,2599]" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Chaetodipus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="20" pageNumber="213" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="siccus">C. siccus</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="73944D33875BB101127A5C1CF626F5DA" baseAuthorityName="Merriam" baseAuthorityYear="1889" box="[2339,2482,2574,2599]" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Chaetodipus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="20" pageNumber="213" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="spinatus">C. spinatus</taxonomicName>
. Eight subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
